  "text": "The G1 garbage collector's concurrent marking and mixed collection cycle in OpenJDK/JDK is implemented through a coordinated chain of C++ classes and methods. The cycle is initiated by VM_G1TryInitiateConcMark (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1VMOperations.cpp) which triggers the start of the concurrent marking phase. G1ConcurrentMark (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentMark.cpp) manages the core marking data structures and lifecycle. The cycle begins with pre_concurrent_start() which sets up internal state, followed by concurrent_cycle_start() which registers the GC start with timing infrastructure. G1ConcurrentMarkThread (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentMarkThread.cpp) orchestrates the marking phases: phase_scan_root_regions() initiates root region scanning via G1ConcurrentMark::scan_root_regions(), which processes regions created during young GC collection. The main concurrent marking phase is executed through phase_mark_loop() which calls subphase_mark_from_roots(), launching G1ConcurrentMark::mark_from_roots(). This spawns G1CMConcurrentMarkingTask workers that execute G1CMTask::do_marking_step() - the core work loop that performs graph traversal of live objects. During marking, G1CMTask::drain_satb_buffers() processes the SATB (Snapshot-At-The-Beginning) marking queues (G1SATBMarkQueueSet in src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1SATBMarkQueueSet.cpp) to handle write barriers during concurrent execution. For remembered set operations, G1RemSet (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1RemSet.cpp) provides scan_heap_roots() for scanning heap references during evacuation and merge_heap_roots() for consolidating dirty card information. Mixed collection region selection is handled by G1CollectionSetChooser::build() (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1CollectionSetChooser.cpp), which uses G1BuildCandidateRegionsTask to evaluate old generation regions based on garbage reclamation efficiency, computing live_bytes from concurrent marking results and filtering regions with low occupancy. The cycle concludes with phase_cleanup() invoking G1ConcurrentMark::cleanup() to reclaim empty regions and finalize marking data structures, followed by concurrent_cycle_end() which completes timing and tracing of the marking cycle. This entire chain ensures that object liveness is tracked concurrently while maintaining SATB invariants, enabling efficient mixed-mode garbage collection that can quickly identify and evacuate low-efficiency old regions identified during marking."
